<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-06T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-06T18:00:00-05:00" n="584" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 825.6374/61</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-06T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Supplementing Department’s December 4th regarding nitrates. In case
                            acceptance of proposal in paragraph 3 is made conditional upon including
                                <persName corresp="#p_MWG1">Gibbs</persName> among purchasers for
                            American market on basis of their fair proportion of past business, you
                            are authorized to assent to that arrangement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>